The core product (what users actually get)

Smart assessment (5–15 questions)
User answers about:

Interests, subjects they enjoy

Skills (logical, creative, communication, technical)

Constraints (budget, location, family expectations, time)

Goal (money, stability, passion, abroad, government job, etc.)

Career path report (the “magic moment”)
Bridge Coach returns 3–5 recommended paths, each with:

Field Example

Path name

“Software Engineer via B.Tech CSE”

Fit score

82/100 (how well it matches them)

Pros

High demand, remote jobs, good salary growth

Cons

Competitive exams, long study hours

Earning range (India)

₹4–8 LPA fresher → ₹15–40 LPA mid-career

Success factors

Math strength, consistency, projects

Next 3 steps

Pick PCM → prepare JEE/boards → build coding basics

Ongoing coach (subscription value)
Weekly/monthly action plans

“You’re in Class 11 now — here’s this month’s focus”

Interview prep, college applications, skill courses

Life-stage upgrades — when they pass Class 12, the coach shifts to college mode automatically

“Success accuracy” — say it the right way

Don’t promise: “90% success guaranteed.”

Do offer: Path Fit Score + Effort Reality Check

Example:
Path Fit: 78/100 — Strong match for your analytical skills and interest in tech.

Effort level: High (competitive exams + 4 years degree).

Market demand (India): High in IT/services.

Estimated timeline to first good job: 4–6 years if consistent.

This is honest, legal, and still very valuable. Parents and students trust clarity, not hype.

